notesStmt.note: Incipit and explicit: "Apicii Celii Epimeles Liber Primus incipit foeliciter (f. 1r) ... "Apicii Celii Alieveslibus [sic] liber Decimus et Ultimus explicit foeliciter" (f. 29v).
The word "Diligentia" is written over "Epimeles" in the incipit, in a later hand.
Bound with printed text: Platina, 1421-1481. Platynae de honesta voluptate. Venice, 1475. (Goff P-762). Shelved as Folio Inc P-762.

msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Cookery book attributed to Apicius. Appears to consist of excerpts from the De re coquinaria. In ten sections or books, each with its own title or heading.

supportDesc.extent: 29 leaves : 288 x 205 (193 x 130) mm. bound to 289 x 204 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 29; [1-29]; modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 33 long lines; ruled in drypoint.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in an Italian humanistic script.

binding.p: Q leather over wooden boards, single metal clasp with leather strap.

origin.p: Written in Italy in the last quarter of the 15th century.

history.provenance: Formerly owned by C. S. Ascherson (bookplate, inside upper cover).
